{"session_id":"svc-1778111977808528606","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-06T23:59:37.962608233Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"gpt-5.4-mini","sticky":{"key_present":true,"assignment":"not_applicable"},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"resolved_harness":"codex","harness_source":"auto_route","resolved_model":"gpt-5.4-mini","work_dir":"/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-66c98cde-20260506T235935-b3a79f34","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead is too big when any of these holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate top-level deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across more than ~5 files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, treat Step 0 as a split-first pass and favor child-bead scoping before implementation.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, decomposed children may split once more, and third-level splits must be rejected with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (focused title, description, AC; copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;` so the decomposition is visible.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260506T235935-b3a79f34/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing each child ID and slice, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a successful attempt. Do not mix partial implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260506T235935-b3a79f34/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If you write `.ddx/executions/20260506T235935-b3a79f34/no_changes_rationale.txt`, it MUST carry one of:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;one-line shell command\u0026gt;` — the loop runs it (cwd = project root, 60s); exit 0 closes the bead, non-zero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: needs_investigation` + `reason: \u0026lt;why\u0026gt;` — bead stays open for triage.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Bare rationales (\u0026#34;nothing to do\u0026#34;) are rejected.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260506T235935-b3a79f34/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260506T235935-b3a79f34/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Bead overrides project defaults\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead description and AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and conservative project defaults (YAGNI, DOWITYTD, no-docs-unless-asked) in this worktree — write whatever the bead asks for.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-66c98cde\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003ework: keep provider outages retryable instead of triage-parked\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;A transient route/provider outage parked 23 open beads behind `triage:needs-investigation`. Their latest actionable event was `execute-bead summary=execution_failed` with detail/body `execute-loop: all tiers exhausted — no viable provider found`. Once routing recovered, these beads remained excluded from `ddx work` until an operator manually removed the triage label.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_status.go:103-108 already classifies `no viable harness`, `no harness configured`, `failed to initialize routing service`, and `no viable provider` as FailureModeNoViableProvider.\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/agent/try/attempt.go:496-499 and cli/internal/agent/ratelimit_retry.go:137-142 explicitly exclude `no viable provider` from rate-limit retry handling, so this path does not get the bounded HTTP-429 retry treatment.\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:1191-1195 runs post-attempt triage for non-preserved execution failures and can then suppress progress with cooldown/triage metadata. In the observed queue, that produced durable `triage:needs-investigation` labels for transient provider outages.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;Handle FailureModeNoViableProvider as a retryable transport outage, not a needs-investigation condition. A no-viable-provider attempt should unclaim the bead and either set a short retry cooldown or leave it retryable according to the existing retry policy, but it must not add or preserve `triage:needs-investigation` solely because routing was unavailable. `ddx work` diagnostics should distinguish provider outage from human-investigation blockers.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;IN-SCOPE FILES\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_status.go\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop_test.go\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/bead/reconcile.go and reconcile tests if stale labels need cleanup semantics\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;- Do not treat quota exhaustion as HTTP 429 rate-limit retry; keep the current rate-limit contract boundary.\u0026#xA;- Do not remove `triage:needs-investigation` for genuine `status: needs_investigation` no_changes rationales.\u0026#xA;- Do not change Fizeau routing or model selection.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. TestExecuteBeadWorker_NoViableProviderDoesNotAddNeedsInvestigation verifies an execution_failed report classified as FailureModeNoViableProvider leaves the bead open/retryable without `triage:needs-investigation`.\u0026#xA;2. TestExecuteBeadWorker_NoViableProviderUsesRetryableTransportPolicy verifies the bead is unclaimed and either has the intended short retry cooldown or is immediately retryable per the chosen policy; it must not be parked as human investigation.\u0026#xA;3. TestReconcile_NoViableProviderClearsStaleNeedsInvestigation verifies a bead whose latest event is no-viable-provider has stale `triage:needs-investigation` removed by reconcile/cleanup if that path owns cleanup.\u0026#xA;4. TestExecuteBeadWorker_NeedsInvestigationRationaleStillParks verifies genuine `status: needs_investigation` no_changes behavior is unchanged.\u0026#xA;5. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/agent/... ./internal/bead/... -run \u0026#34;TestExecuteBeadWorker_NoViableProvider|TestReconcile_NoViableProvider|TestExecuteBeadWorker_NeedsInvestigationRationaleStillParks\u0026#34; -count=1 passes.\u0026#xA;6. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:2, area:agent, area:routing, area:beads, kind:bug, reliability, prevention, spec:FEAT-010\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-f3dfde0d\" spec-id=\"FEAT-010\" base-rev=\"6e534706a15fb81596a7488710732a98ff73e169\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260506T235935-b3a79f34\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cref id=\"FEAT-010\" path=\"docs/helix/01-frame/features/FEAT-010-task-execution.md\"\u003eFeature: Task Execution\u003c/ref\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"attempt_id":"20260506T235935-b3a79f34","base_rev":"6e5347